section.section:
Of the 17 members:
one member shall represent a telephone company operating in the State;
one member shall represent the wireless telephone industry in the State;
one member shall represent the Maryland Institute for Emergency Medical Services Systems;
one member shall represent the Department of State Police;
one member shall represent the Public Service Commission;
one member shall represent the Association of Public-Safety Communications Officials International, Inc.;
two members shall represent county fire services in the State, with one member representing career fire services and one member representing volunteer fire services;
one member shall represent police services in the State;
two members shall represent emergency management services in the State;
one member shall represent a county with a population of 200,000 or more;
one member shall represent a county with a population of less than 200,000;
one member shall represent the Maryland chapter of the National Emergency Numbers Association;
one member shall represent the geographical information systems in the State; and
two members shall represent the public.
